Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with cornucopia (plus) symbol.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Pencil '17'. Name Sosiphilos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0012.35.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (Possibly, but could equally well be a Newton find.)
Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (Perhaps, but could be a Petrie find)
